      • GetAlternateUrls

        protected static Set<String> GetAlternateUrls(String url,
                           Connection perf)
                                       throws MalformedURLException
        Alternate URLs, basically multiple hostnames, FQDN, host file entries, etc can map to the same service. Sometimes a particular url is firewalled or only listens on a specific hostname. By default bueller will first attempt a connection using the modified url, i.e. the URL displayed in fgsms which usually uses the hostname of the machine hosting the service If another url was observed by an agent at some point in time, then this will fetch all other urls for
